      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARIN NZ (1) started from a much wider barrier last week so there was merit in his effort to finish midfield. Placed in his previous three outings including a narrow defeat at this circuit and distance prior. Should get his chance from the ace draw. FORCE FULL (4) continued his good form when he came from a wide draw to miss narrowly at Newcastle last start. Recorded back-to-back placings at this venue last month. Could break through. PICCADILLY PETE NZ (5) should find this easier than the last attempt and had placed in his other two starts this time in, coming from wider for second here two back. Can bounce back. MASTER CATCH (10) draws deep but was good here last start when he worked but boxed on to go under by only 2m. PROMISING (2) did a good job to place last start and draws to advantage.",
